BACKGROUND: Treatment for patients with breast cancer (BC) is guided by human 
epidermal growth factor receptor 2 (HER2) status. The patient's HER2 status is 
assessed using US Food and Drug Administration-approved in vitro diagnostic 
(IVD) immunohistochemical (IHC) tests and laboratory-developed IVD tests. We 
analysed HER2 testing accuracy using data from the Nordic Immunohistochemistry 
